<br>
1: The epic should be the best pet ever camp<br>
<br>
2: Get over it, new pets should be better camp.<br>
<br>
Well there is a 3rd camp and we should speak in a unified voice to get it approved in MHO. It is this:<br>
<br>
Let the Orb become a focus item on the Post Greater Vocerate pets ONLY.<br>
<br>
It will focus them but not the epic which it will still summon. <br>
<br>
Yes I know of the focus gloves in VT and they would still focus all pets from level 65 on down, but this will allow all mages who finish our quest have a post level 60 focus item, for all their hard work.<br>
<br>
Verant has shown they can level restrict focus items, as well as 2 effects to every item, so it is doable.<br>
<br>
So how about it, you worked hard for the epic. You have it, and at level 61 (if your lucky and get the new pet), you wield your Orb as you summon the new pet, and it is focused. yes it is better than the epic pet, but it is a lot better than the non focused pet as well. So it makes doing the quest very valuable.<br>
<br>
Thoughts and suggestions, and if we all agree, lets push it through, after all, it is the orb of Elemental Mastery, so let it focus the 61 and greater pets.<br>
<br>
As I said in my other post it is a Win/Win for any magician who did the Epic Quest.<br>
<br>
