<br>
Is idealy what I would love to happen.  <br>
<br>
Granted, nobody knows if a 2nd epic quest is even in the game, or will be... But I think it should.<br>
<br>
Forget epic being a focus item honestly... I also want the epic to be some sort of a progression... But twords a second and more powerfull epic would be a better idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etadanikm>EtadanikM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(11/6/02 6:22:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7761.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Consider this for a bit...</span><hr size=1> Would VI really do this? I mean, if they make the epic a focus item, they are then systematically increasing the power of level 61+ mages with the epic by a sizeable margin, depending on how powerful the epic's focus effect is (if it's one level, no big deal, but would that really be &quot;epic&quot;?)<br>
<br>
Would they do this out of nothing? Would they increase mage power (and thus mage balance) for free? Somehow I doubt it.  Somehow I think they're going to factor this into account with overall balance if they are going to implement it, and if they do that...<br>
<br>
They might nerf mage pets 61+ overall, to justify this change, or<br>
perhaps they might use it to justify mages being &quot;balanced&quot;, thus once again requiring mages to complete their epics in order to be balanced with other classes.<br>
<br>
Is that really desirable? Consider it.  A powerful focus effect is a general increase in power to the mage class, regardless of level, and unlike most other classes' epics it is a linear increase: you get a stronger pet regardless of your level.  If this comes to fruit, then it is necessary to consider whether every other classes' epics should ALSO be similarly improved, and that's just asking to open a can 'o worms.<br>
<br>
Remember, the &quot;other&quot; camp's argument is more than that the newer pets should be better than the epic, but rather that the epic, like any other item in the game, should, in time, become obsolete and be replaced.<br>
<br>
What you're asking for is to make the magic epic useful, always and forever, and never decrease in its relative usefulness.  This is currently true of only three epics, all of them priestly: the cleric epic (clickly rez will always be useful), the shaman epic (they get no magic based dot but this), and the druid epic (stackable with all their dots).  The wizard (forceshield &gt; effect and doesn't stack, I think), necro (embracing darkness &gt; effect and doesn't stack), enchanter (new hastes &gt; effect and overwrites), and just about every melee epic have decreased in power, and continue to do so as players become stronger.<br>
<br>
Is it really fair for the mage epic to go the way of the priestly epics?<br>
